Dream of life
First chapter storyboard...
Complete!
It is way better than before!
Yeah, even I can tell!
Shujin, let Hattori know.
Right!
In only five days, they have redone it from scratch and taken it this far!
It is much better!
Oh thank goodness.
I suppose you two did not get much sleep?
So,
how else can we fix it?!
Can it get better?!
So that it can definitely beat Niizuma!
Let us see.
Is the title okay as is?
Perfect Crime Club...
It may be a bit stiff.
Yeah...
It should be more shounen manga-like.
Well, there is the tried and true method of putting the protagonist's name in the title.
Like Captain Tsubasa?
Yeah.
Tanto was like that, too.
That way you know right away what it is about and who is the main character.
It is certainly easy to tell from that, and it is simple and easy to remember.
If that is the case, then...
Chimitsu Kei... it does not leave much of an impression.
It may be too plain for a main character.
Oozora Tsubasa.
Sakuragi Hanamichi.
You want a well-defined name with as much impact as those.
A name suitable for a main character...
Speaking of main characters, there is one more thing you need to fix.
One more thing?
A design suitable for a main character.
Since the setting calls for a normal elementary school kid, we want it to be realistic,
so to a certain degree it is okay, but he is just too normal right now.
There is no difference between him and his classmates.
The impact of his appearance...
This is more important than his name, is not it?
You are right.
He needs to have a special characteristic.
I will do his character design.
Takagi, you worry about the name and the title.
Let us redo all the main characters' names, not just his.
Got it.
I will think of them as soon as I can.
You do not have to hurry with the names, since we can just cut and paste them in.
But the character design needs to come first, so I have to hurry.
I have given them all the advice I can.
I will leave the rest to them.
I have got you two assistants.
I have made sure they are suited to your art style.
Oh, and we have got Orihara on board, too.
Counting backwards... we will make it if we start the manuscript around the 13th.
The 13th is the New Year's party.
Oh, right.
If we have a new serialization, we have to go, do not we?
The New Year's party.
I want to do what my uncle could not do, and the things he left undone.
What he could not do?
What he left undone?
What he could not do was make a living off of manga alone.
What he left undone was getting first place in the rankings!
Is the coming of age ceremony over already?
How could I let you keep working alone when I have not come up with character names or a title yet?
Iwase and Ishizawa were there too, so we ducked out early.
But you have really drawn a lot of them.
There must be a hundred.
I have drawn everything I could think of.
Is there one that jumps out at you?
You are the one who knows the most about art.
I am good with whatever you come up with.
I have not come up with anything yet, which is why I am still drawing.
Since we want to keep things realistic, there is a limit to what I can do with the hair.
Ugh, I do not want an elementary school kid looking like that.
I know!
I guess we cannot go to today's New Year's party, after all.
Oh, it is Abe!
We saw each other at the ceremony.
Hey!
Yeah.
I am not home yet.
Huh?
Right now?
Both of us?
Ashirogi is not coming?
What a shame.
They are working hard, are not they?
I am happy.
I cannot believe they would give up this brief time of enjoyment.
So...
What is up with that outfit, Akira?
It is punishment for the editors whose authors did not show up.
And you, Yuujirou?
Fukuda is still drawing his manuscript.
Boss Fukuda is not here either?!
What are these people thinking?
Hiramaru.
We will have to work harder, too.
Let the hardworking folks work hard.
Meanwhile, I can take a break.
I am living large with these Otter figures selling like pancakes!
Do you want one, too?
An Otter figure
Aoki!
Hiramaru, I misjudged you.
You are conceited.
Hey
I was just joking!
Hey, wait!
You got what you deserved, Hiramaru.
Oh, Akina!
Happy New Year!
Congratulations.
Your latest manuscript was fantastic.
I am counting on you for the rest.
Of course it is.
I will become the best in the business.
I am expecting art that is even better than your usual quality.
Roger!
The editor swap put a fire under Akina.
We have got some powerful rivals, Ashirogi Muto!
Akira!
Yuujirou.
It looks like you are up.
Are we seriously doing this?
And now, the moment you have all been waiting for!
Next up is the Hattori combo, Giraffe Akira and Zebra Yuujirou with Otters 11 !
Hello?
It is Mashiro.
I am sorry we could not make it to the New Year's party.
Do not sweat it, this is part of an editor's job.
Thanks to that, I have finished the character design!
Oh, really?
I will be going back to the officecan you send me a fax?
Yes.
The phone strap idea is good.
The way he changes modes with glasses is not forced.
It is good!
I am glad!
Put this in the manuscript right away.
Right!
It is been a while!
Nice to be working with you again!
You too.
Sorry we made you wait for half a year.
What are you talking about?
I have grown over this past year, and I am ready to bust my tail for you!
The new assistants will be here soon, will not they?
Right.
Moriya and Shiratori, right?
He said they are both younger than us, I think.
It is the first time our assistants will all be younger.
I am getting kind of nervous.
Because you are shy, Saiko.
Oh right, about this Moriya guy...
So he was a finalist for the most recent Tezuka prize.
That is some strange art.
But it is good.
He has design sense.
I could not find anything on Shiratori.
They are here!
This is Moriya.
He is one year younger than you two.
He was attending design school,
but after he was a finalist for the Tezuka prize, he left to draw manga.
Yes.
If I am aiming to be a manga author,
I figured it would be quicker if I start out as an assistant.
This is Shiratori.
He just graduated from high school last year.
He applied to be an assistant for Niizuma,
but his assistants had already been decided on, so I brought him over here.
I did not get in to art school and was wondering what I was going to do...
when I saw the recruitment for assistants.
I love drawing, so I am glad.
You have not actually drawn any manga before, right?
Right.
But I like reading them.
I guarantee their skill.
Looking forward to working with you.
Looking forward to working with you.
You, too.
We are counting on you.
Mashiro.
Yes?
This is your third serialization.
You can take it from here, right?
Yes!
Then I will get going.
Good evening!
Th-Then...
I am going to give you each a copy of two pages of the manuscript with a rough sketch of the backgrounds.
Please draw it in.
I will choose one of you to do backgrounds so that the style does not change from page to page.
So only one of us will be able to draw?
Sounds good to me.
Okay, I will do my best.
Skill is a given, but they need speed and sense, too...
I am finished.
What?
Me, too.
What?!
Please look over it.
Okay,
But I will only decide once Orihara is finished.
I understand.
I am done!
Even I am getting nervous.
Yeah.
I would like to ask...
Shiratori to do backgrounds.
Yay, I get to draw!
That is great, Shiratori!
Congrats!
Why him?!
His art is nearest to what I imagined.
Until the style of this manga is solidified, I will have Shiratori do it.
I understand.
Anyway, this Perfect Crime Club is really good!
Yeah, I like how it is unique.
The title's still a placeholder.
I am planning on changing it.
The main character's name, too.
Really?
As long as we have the time, I am going to keep nitpicking over the details until I am satisfied.
Well, I do not think the title and the main character's name will really affect the rankings.
You are really thinking this through.
Rankings, huh.
There is something wrong about stuff like rankings.
There is no point in drawing manga just to get popular.
But manga is for everyone to enjoy, right?
Popularity is important.
You cannot draw a good manga if you think like that!
Though since you do not draw any manga, I suppose it has nothing to do with you.
Then what is your ideal manga?
To me, manga is a form of self-expression and a fine art.
I believe all manga should be thus.
Fine art, huh?
If you do it that way, you will feel good about yourself, but it will not sell.
Jack is a business,
so the manga has to appeal to a majority of people.
Is not it obvious that rankings and sales figures are important?
To try and draw for Jack without understanding that...
Shiratori, you have gone too far!
Saiko...
Please tell us
your opinion.
We are trying to get this to sell.
But that is because we do not have the talent.
Parents used to say to their kids... well, maybe they are still saying this...
Reading manga makes you stupid.
They would not let them read it.
But manga gradually came to be recognized as having cultural value.
That is why I think you should draw a manga with content and quality that you would not be ashamed to say has cultural value.
But since we do not have the ability to do that, we have to draw it with popularity in mind.
I think it is okay for anyone to draw manga like that, in accordance with their abilities.
Yes, everyone should draw in their own way.
Good work, Mashiro.
Oh, thanks.
I did not know what was going to happen during that argument!
Well, it looks like they are at opposite ends of the spectrum.
It is hard to say who is right or wrong.
Opposites, huh?
Opposite?!
I could turn this around...
I was too caught up with the idea of a perfect crime.
If I think along the lines of them not committing real crimes, then...
What is he saying?
I have got it!
How about this?!
If you put them together, that is morals and truth.
They fit the main characters, since they are the opposite of crime.
Doumoto Makoto.
Tokunaga Minoru.
And Annojo Mai!
They are not bad!
They are kind of cool, even!
They are great.
Let us go with that!
You are awesome, Akito!
This is what happens when I get a flash of intuition.
So what about the title?
I have not got that yet.
That is disappointing.
Well, we still have a few days before we need to finish.
It is a perfect manuscript!
The story and art are a given, but the protagonist's names are good, too!
And this title
Perfect Crime Party.
PCP!
The Japanese translation is Perfect Crime Party.
Right!
I was watching the news and I thought party as in political party would work well.
Party has a cheerful image, and since it is also used in video games, I thought it would make it seem fun.
A typical Takagi analysis.
The effort you two put into this really shows.
Yes!
We will definitely get first place for the first chapter!
We have put everything we possibly could into this to accomplish that!
I think aiming for that with this manuscript is more than reasonable.
The rest depends on Fukuda's one-shot, since that will be in the issue, too.
Fukuda's one-shot?
I did not hear about this!
This is why I said it was impossible to do a one-shot and KIYOSHI at the same time!
You gave me your permission!
That is why I am helping you right now!
But this manga is good!
It is on fire!
Road Racer Buchigiri.
There was a super car boom.
Now I will because a super bike boom!
It is not bad to have a hobby.
It is all because you said that to me, Yuujirou.
I am grateful to you for that.
Well, thanks a bunch!
But I am pissed that it is in the same issue as Ashirogi's first chapter!
It means they want to compare it with a new serialization.
The editorial department put some thought into it.
I feel sorry for Ashirogi Muto!
I will steal the top spot from them with this!
This is the finished sample copy.
It sure is nice to be on the front cover.
Fukuda's manga is good.
It feels like a straightforward shounen.
He drives by girls on purpose to flip up their skirts.
Typical Fukuda.
Both his characters and story are typical mainstream.
I think it is good, too.
Mainstream...
This is going to split the votes.
Fukuda's on a roll.
Making a manga about your hobby sure has a big effect.
But if it comes down to a new serialization and a one-shot, people are more likely to vote for the new serialization, right?
That trend does exist, but it is not a sure thing.
Buchigiri has a clear goal of becoming the number one racer.
The race scenes are showy and intense.
PCP has a lot of exposition and will look plain in comparison.
But the content is good, right?
Yes, it is.
Then...
That is, if they understand what is going on.
The majority of the readers are in their teens.
Buchigiri is easier for them to understand.
Aida, what ranking do you think PCP will get?
If it splits votes with Buchigiri,
then it may be hard for it to get ahead of the other popular manga.
It is all up to the readers.
Hey, the early results are in tomorrow, right?
I have told him to only let us know the final results.
What?
But I really want to know!
Rankings, huh?
Moriya, not again
I would like to know as well.
I hope it does well.
Me, too.
It definitely will!
That is right.
PCP is the manga that must rank highly.
Will we place even with Niizuma?
Or even higher?
I cannot seem to calm down.
Hey, what time will the final results be out?

Mashiro, what time are your assistants coming?
I hope he contacts us before they get here.
Then let us try calling him!
They may be out already!
He will contact us as soon as they are out.
Just calm down.
But...
I read it!
I thought it was really good!
I especially liked the part where they spent two weeks preparing and
in just one night, made a message with flowers in the flower bed.
I wish someone would do that for me.
It will be okay.
See, the assistants came already!
What?
It is not even 4 yet.
Hattori?
I am astonished.
It is the best by far.
422 votes.
A 150 vote lead over 2nd place.
1st place.
Hey, the door's open!
Yes!
We did it!
We did it!
We did it!
We did it!
We did it!
Yeah, we did it!
We got first place!
By a landslide!
You did it, Saiko!
Let me in, too!

CROW got 401.

Natural only got 310 votes!
If there was not a one-shot, how would it have done?
Anyway, it is amazing.
2nd place with 268 votes?

That is frustrating.

Fukuda Shinta should make Buchigiri.
That is what the readers want.
You can wrap up KIYOSHI.
Make a serialization storyboard for Buchigiri!

I will pay them back with a serialization!
They did?
Yes, and by a landslide.
This was only because PCP and Buchigiri were good...
I will rewrite it.
Huh?
I cannot afford to lose to Hattori and Takagi.
I will rewrite everything you have not sent to the printer yet!
So she said she wants to rewrite as much as possible.
Even what I am drawing now?
Yes, if possible...
Akina said she will make it better, right?
That is right.
Roger!
If she was not that fired up, I would be disappointed!
If we do not make it better, Ashirogi will overtake us!
Under 10 and over 18?
Yeah.
The main demographic voted too, but those two age ranges were particularly conspicuous.
Let us analyze that and use it for reference going forward.
All right!
Let us set aside the difficult issues for now, since Hattori went out of his way to bring us a feast!
Before I realized it, I was at the grocery store...
Hattori.
Can I have the results chart?
No.
Even though you are an author, I cannot give it to you.
Do you want it as a keepsake?
No, I have someone I want to show it to.

Other authors' rankings are on here.
I have no problem with you telling your own rank to others, though.
Then...
Would you come with me?
Okay.
Is it okay for me to come, too?
There is no point if we are not together.
This is...
Uncle...
This is what you wanted, but never managed to get.
A first place ranking in Weekly Shounen Jack.
It is not like I got this all by myself.
Many people helped me.
But Ashirogi Muto got 1st place!
So what if your first chapter got first place?
Of course it would.
Back when Fist of the North Star was popular, it got first place with more than 700 votes.
The real challenge starts from here, right?
When you get really popular and are truly number one,
come back here.
Of course I will!
Six months.
We will see how it goes until their 25th chapter.
If they get such low rankings that it should be canceled, then after their 7th chapter, I will not hesitate.
And if they are not head to head with CROW and +NATURAL by chapter 25,
I will cancel it right then and there.

but the anime still goes on!
Can Ashirogi
